WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
William Tell, by Friedrich von Schiller, Penguin Reader's Level 1, Scene 1, in Outdorf, Switzerland.

00:13.000 --> 00:16.000
This is an important day.

00:16.000 --> 00:19.000
We're going to meet with Governor Gessler.

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
We can't be late.

00:21.000 --> 00:29.000
Our Austrian emperor and his governors don't understand the Swiss people.

00:29.000 --> 00:36.000
We aren't Austrians, we're Swiss, and we love our country.

00:36.000 --> 00:41.000
And we don't want to give our money to Austria.

00:41.000 --> 00:44.000
Here's one of Gessler's soldiers.

00:44.000 --> 00:46.000
It's time.

00:46.000 --> 00:49.000
Let's go in and talk.

00:49.000 --> 00:54.000
Gessler must understand our problems.

00:55.000 --> 01:00.000
What do you want now?

01:00.000 --> 01:07.000
You Swiss people come here every day with a new problem.

01:07.000 --> 01:10.000
Our problems aren't new.

01:10.000 --> 01:13.000
You never listen to us.

01:13.000 --> 01:17.000
Things are difficult in Switzerland these days.

01:17.000 --> 01:21.000
Difficult? I don't understand.

01:22.000 --> 01:26.000
Your soldiers are always watching us.

01:26.000 --> 01:31.000
Every day you put a new tax on us.

01:31.000 --> 01:38.000
There are taxes on our food, our houses, and our animals.

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
How can we live with these taxes?

01:42.000 --> 01:49.000
Perhaps you can't, but I can live very well with them.

01:49.000 --> 01:53.000
And the emperor is happy with them too.

01:53.000 --> 01:56.000
But we're very unhappy.

01:56.000 --> 01:59.000
We don't want to be Austrians.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
We're Swiss.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Please listen to us.

02:03.000 --> 02:08.000
Your Austrian emperor is very good to you.

02:08.000 --> 02:11.000
But you don't understand him.

02:11.000 --> 02:16.000
That's right, and he doesn't understand us.

02:16.000 --> 02:20.000
This is our country now.

02:20.000 --> 02:21.000
Go home.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.000
Listen to me and to the emperor.

02:25.000 --> 02:34.000
Or things are going to get very dangerous for every Swiss man, woman, and child.

02:34.000 --> 02:35.000
Go.

02:35.000 --> 02:38.000
I don't want to talk to you.

02:38.000 --> 02:43.000
My time is important, and you are not.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
What did the governor say?

02:50.000 --> 02:54.000
Is he going to send his soldiers back to Austria?

02:54.000 --> 02:58.000
Is he going to stop putting taxes on us?

02:58.000 --> 03:02.000
Did he understand our problems?

03:02.000 --> 03:06.000
No. He didn't listen to us.

03:06.000 --> 03:09.000
What can we do?

03:09.000 --> 03:12.000
Can we stop this man?

03:12.000 --> 03:15.000
Perhaps we can.

03:15.000 --> 03:19.000
But first, we must find a hero.

03:19.000 --> 03:22.000
A Swiss hero.

03:28.000 --> 03:33.000
Scene two. At a river in the Swiss mountains.

03:36.000 --> 03:39.000
I'm going home now.

03:39.000 --> 03:42.000
Look, it's going to rain.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
Get my boat from the river.

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
It's getting cold.

03:46.000 --> 03:48.000
And the water looks dangerous.

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
Winter's coming.

03:50.000 --> 03:52.000
Good night, Rudy.

03:52.000 --> 03:55.000
Wait. Look. Who's coming?

03:55.000 --> 03:57.000
I know that man.

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
It's Conrad Baumgarten.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
Help me, my friends.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
Boatman, quick.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
Take me across the river now.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
Or I'm a dead man.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
Please.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
What's the problem?

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
Who wants to kill you?

04:14.000 --> 04:16.000
Guessler's men.

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
They're coming. Quick.

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
Why are they looking for you?

04:20.000 --> 04:23.000
I killed one of the governor's tax men.

04:23.000 --> 04:25.000
I was at work.

04:25.000 --> 04:27.000
Away from home.

04:27.000 --> 04:30.000
The man came to my house.

04:30.000 --> 04:34.000
He asked my wife for water.

04:34.000 --> 04:37.000
And then he wanted hers.

04:37.000 --> 04:40.000
My wife came to me for help.

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
I went home quickly.

04:42.000 --> 04:45.000
And then I killed him with my knife.

04:45.000 --> 04:48.000
You did well.

04:48.000 --> 04:50.000
Rudy, quick.

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
Take him across the river in your boat.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.000
I can't.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
The river's moving very quickly.

04:57.000 --> 04:59.000
And the rain is heavy.

04:59.000 --> 05:02.000
No boat can go across the river now.

05:02.000 --> 05:05.000
Rudy, you must help this man.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.000
He has a family.

05:07.000 --> 05:11.000
I have a wife and three sons too.

05:11.000 --> 05:14.000
Look at the river. It's dangerous.

05:14.000 --> 05:17.000
I want to help, but I can't.

05:17.000 --> 05:19.000
And I'm dead.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.000
A man is coming.

05:21.000 --> 05:24.000
Oh, it's William Tell.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Good evening, my friends.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
What's wrong here?

05:28.000 --> 05:32.000
Bound Garden killed one of the governor's tax men.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
The soldiers are looking for him.

05:34.000 --> 05:38.000
But our boatman can't take him across the river.

05:38.000 --> 05:41.000
The river's dangerous. Look at it.

05:41.000 --> 05:44.000
But Bound Garden can't wait here.

05:44.000 --> 05:46.000
What can we do?

05:46.000 --> 05:49.000
There's my boat, and there's the river.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.000
You can take the boat and be the hero.

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
I'm going to stay here.

05:55.000 --> 05:56.000
Bound Garden.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
Let's go quickly.

05:58.000 --> 06:01.000
Bernie, send my love to my family.

06:05.000 --> 06:13.000
Scene three.

06:13.000 --> 06:16.000
At Stalfucka's home.

06:16.000 --> 06:20.000
Your story isn't new.

06:20.000 --> 06:24.000
The emperor's governors, his Austrian soldiers,

06:24.000 --> 06:30.000
and his tax men make new problems for us every day.

06:30.000 --> 06:34.000
Kessler is playing games with our country.

06:34.000 --> 06:37.000
We don't want to kill people.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
We don't want to fight.

06:39.000 --> 06:41.000
We're men of peace.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.000
But what can we do?

06:43.000 --> 06:48.000
Let's find a number of good, strong Swiss men.

06:48.000 --> 06:51.000
We must stop these Austrians.

06:51.000 --> 06:55.000
I'm going to visit Walter first tomorrow.

06:55.000 --> 06:58.000
He loves our country.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
He can help us.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
We must fight for our country.

07:02.000 --> 07:04.000
Let's start now.

07:04.000 --> 07:07.000
Yes, we must help our country.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
But can't we find peace?

07:10.000 --> 07:12.000
I'm going home.

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
My family are waiting.

07:14.000 --> 07:19.000
But remember, you can always ask for my help.

07:23.000 --> 07:25.000
Scene four.

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
Hello.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.000
You're the famous governor, Kessler.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
Am I right?

07:33.000 --> 07:34.000
You're right.

07:34.000 --> 07:36.000
And who are you?

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
My name's William Tell.

07:38.000 --> 07:41.000
I'm a hunter, and I'm Swiss.

07:41.000 --> 07:44.000
That's interesting.

07:44.000 --> 07:47.000
But I haven't got time for you.

07:47.000 --> 07:52.000
I'm an important man with important work in my life.

07:52.000 --> 07:56.000
Why do I want to talk to you?

07:56.000 --> 07:59.000
Because this is my country.

07:59.000 --> 08:04.000
You're making problems for us with your taxes and your soldiers.

08:04.000 --> 08:08.000
The people of this country are very unhappy.

08:08.000 --> 08:10.000
Wait.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.000
William Tell.

08:12.000 --> 08:15.000
I want to talk to you.

08:15.000 --> 08:18.000
Because this is my country.

08:18.000 --> 08:21.000
You're making problems for us with your taxes and your soldiers.

08:21.000 --> 08:24.000
Well, I know about you.

08:24.000 --> 08:27.000
You helped Baumgarten.

08:27.000 --> 08:31.000
Yes, but Baumgarten is a good man.

08:31.000 --> 08:36.000
He killed your tax man because the man was dangerous.

08:36.000 --> 08:40.000
Aren't you a dangerous man too?

08:40.000 --> 08:44.000
Don't you always have a crossbow with you?

08:44.000 --> 08:49.000
Don't you go into the mountains every day and kill?

08:49.000 --> 08:51.000
I kill animals.

08:51.000 --> 08:54.000
I put food on my family's table.

08:54.000 --> 08:57.000
I don't kill people.

08:57.000 --> 08:59.000
Can your soldiers say that?

08:59.000 --> 09:02.000
I haven't got time for your talk.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.000
Move.

09:03.000 --> 09:04.000
Now.

09:04.000 --> 09:05.000
Why?

09:05.000 --> 09:07.000
It's not late.

09:07.000 --> 09:08.000
Please.

09:08.000 --> 09:10.000
Listen to me.

09:10.000 --> 09:14.000
You and your taxes are bad for Switzerland.

09:14.000 --> 09:16.000
We don't want you here.

09:16.000 --> 09:19.000
But I am here.

09:19.000 --> 09:22.000
And I'm going to stay.

09:22.000 --> 09:25.000
This is a new Switzerland.

09:25.000 --> 09:28.000
And you must listen to us.

09:28.000 --> 09:33.000
And you must understand the Swiss people.

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
We love our country.

09:35.000 --> 09:38.000
Our mountains and our families.

09:38.000 --> 09:41.000
We want peace.

09:41.000 --> 09:44.000
And we're going to fight for it.

09:44.000 --> 09:51.000
Watch us.

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
Scene five.

09:53.000 --> 09:57.000
At William Tell's home.

09:57.000 --> 10:00.000
You're going to have problems with Gessler now.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.000
Why?

10:01.000 --> 10:03.000
I talked to him.

10:03.000 --> 10:05.000
I didn't hit him.

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
But he's going to remember you.

10:07.000 --> 10:10.000
He's going to make problems for us.

10:10.000 --> 10:12.000
Wait and see.

10:12.000 --> 10:15.000
I'm a man of peace.

10:15.000 --> 10:18.000
I'm going to stay away from Gessler now.

10:18.000 --> 10:20.000
Please do that.

10:20.000 --> 10:22.000
Where are Valta and Wilhelm?

10:22.000 --> 10:24.000
They're in the garden.

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
They're playing a game.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.000
Look at them.

10:27.000 --> 10:29.000
They're little soldiers.

10:29.000 --> 10:31.000
William, this isn't good.

10:31.000 --> 10:35.000
My sons aren't going to be soldiers.

10:35.000 --> 10:40.000
I want peace in my country and in my family.

10:40.000 --> 10:43.000
I understand, Hedwig.

10:43.000 --> 10:46.000
Our sons are going to be hunters.

10:46.000 --> 10:51.000
But one day, our country is going to want soldiers too.

10:51.000 --> 10:57.000
At that time, every man, woman and child must fight for Switzerland.

10:57.000 --> 11:00.000
William, can't you go to the Emperor?

11:00.000 --> 11:04.000
Can't you and your friends talk to him about peace?

11:04.000 --> 11:07.000
Yes, we're going to try.

11:08.000 --> 11:11.000
Father, are we going to outdoor now?

11:11.000 --> 11:13.000
Yes, my son.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.000
Have you got your crossbow?

11:15.000 --> 11:17.000
Why is he taking his crossbow?

11:17.000 --> 11:19.000
I'm a hunter.

11:19.000 --> 11:23.000
I want to teach my son about the mountains and about hunting.

11:23.000 --> 11:25.000
He's a good student.

11:25.000 --> 11:28.000
But the mountains are dangerous for a young boy.

11:28.000 --> 11:31.000
We're mountain people.

11:31.000 --> 11:34.000
This country isn't dangerous for us.

11:34.000 --> 11:37.000
I'm going to watch Valter and teach him.

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
And why are you going to outdoor?

11:40.000 --> 11:42.000
We're going to visit your father.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.000
I want to talk to him.

11:44.000 --> 11:47.000
My father and his friends want to start a fight.

11:47.000 --> 11:49.000
Please don't go William.

11:49.000 --> 11:51.000
You're a man of peace.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.000
I must go.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.000
I must help Switzerland too.

11:55.000 --> 11:58.000
But guesslers in outdoor today.

11:58.000 --> 12:00.000
He doesn't like you.

12:00.000 --> 12:02.000
Stay at home and go tomorrow.

12:02.000 --> 12:03.000
No.

12:03.000 --> 12:05.000
I must go today.

12:05.000 --> 12:06.000
Let's go Valter.

12:06.000 --> 12:08.000
Valter mustn't go.

12:08.000 --> 12:09.000
Please.

12:09.000 --> 12:11.000
He can stay with me.

12:11.000 --> 12:13.000
I want to go with Father.

12:13.000 --> 12:16.000
I want to see the town and the people.

12:16.000 --> 12:18.000
Hedwig.

12:18.000 --> 12:20.000
He's going to be okay with me.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
Scene six.

12:27.000 --> 12:29.000
In Alstorf.

12:30.000 --> 12:37.000
Switzerland has an Austrian emperor and Austrian taxes.

12:37.000 --> 12:43.000
But the Swiss people are always a problem.

12:43.000 --> 12:44.000
Hmm.

12:44.000 --> 12:49.000
What problems can I give them today?

12:49.000 --> 12:52.000
Give them a new tax.

12:52.000 --> 12:53.000
No.

12:53.000 --> 12:56.000
There was a new tax yesterday.

12:57.000 --> 13:01.000
You stopped games on Saturdays and Sundays too.

13:01.000 --> 13:04.000
And you closed the cafes.

13:04.000 --> 13:10.000
You can stop all music after six o'clock in the evening.

13:10.000 --> 13:11.000
Yes.

13:11.000 --> 13:13.000
Very interesting.

13:13.000 --> 13:15.000
But I'm thinking.

13:15.000 --> 13:17.000
What?

13:17.000 --> 13:19.000
What can you do?

13:19.000 --> 13:20.000
Ah.

13:20.000 --> 13:25.000
There's a tall thin tree in front of my office.

13:25.000 --> 13:29.000
Bring me one of my old hats.

13:29.000 --> 13:34.000
Now put the hat on the tree.

13:34.000 --> 13:39.000
Then I want to talk to the people.

13:39.000 --> 13:48.000
People of Switzerland.

13:48.000 --> 13:54.000
You can see a hat on the tree in front of you.

13:55.000 --> 13:57.000
Why is it there?

13:57.000 --> 14:00.000
Can you think?

14:00.000 --> 14:02.000
We don't know.

14:02.000 --> 14:04.000
Is it important?

14:04.000 --> 14:08.000
It's very important to you.

14:08.000 --> 14:12.000
You all love me and your emperor.

14:12.000 --> 14:15.000
Is that right?

14:15.000 --> 14:17.000
What did she say?

14:17.000 --> 14:19.000
She's happy.

14:19.000 --> 14:20.000
That's all.

14:20.000 --> 14:27.000
You can't see me every day because I have a lot of important work.

14:27.000 --> 14:33.000
But you can stop every day and look at my hat.

14:33.000 --> 14:39.000
You can send your love to the emperor and to me too.

14:39.000 --> 14:41.000
Oh God.

14:41.000 --> 14:42.000
Our love.

14:42.000 --> 14:44.000
How can we love a hat?

14:44.000 --> 14:46.000
All the Austrians.

14:46.000 --> 14:49.000
Must we stop for your old hat?

14:49.000 --> 14:50.000
Yes.

14:50.000 --> 14:55.000
All of you must stop.

14:55.000 --> 14:59.000
My soldiers are going to be here every day.

14:59.000 --> 15:03.000
They're going to watch you.

15:09.000 --> 15:11.000
Scene seven.

15:11.000 --> 15:17.000
In front of the tree with the hat.

15:17.000 --> 15:20.000
People aren't going to walk here.

15:20.000 --> 15:23.000
They don't want to stop for a hat.

15:23.000 --> 15:27.000
Perhaps they don't love the emperor and his governor.

15:27.000 --> 15:30.000
But it's only a hat.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
It's not on the emperor's head.

15:32.000 --> 15:36.000
I don't want to make problems for people.

15:36.000 --> 15:40.000
But this is our job.

15:40.000 --> 15:42.000
Look.

15:42.000 --> 15:45.000
A man and a boy are coming.

15:45.000 --> 15:47.000
Let's watch them.

15:47.000 --> 15:52.000
Father, does every country have tall beautiful mountains?

15:52.000 --> 15:57.000
No, son. Switzerland is famous for its mountains.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.000
We Swiss understand them.

15:59.000 --> 16:02.000
And I'm going to teach you.

16:02.000 --> 16:06.000
Look, Father, why is there a hat on that tree?

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
I don't know.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
But it's not important.

16:10.000 --> 16:11.000
Let's go.

16:11.000 --> 16:12.000
Stop.

16:12.000 --> 16:20.000
In the name of the emperor of Austria, stop and look up at the hat.

16:20.000 --> 16:21.000
No.

16:21.000 --> 16:22.000
Why?

16:22.000 --> 16:25.000
No questions.

16:25.000 --> 16:26.000
Come with us.

16:26.000 --> 16:28.000
What are you talking about?

16:28.000 --> 16:30.000
You're coming with us.

16:30.000 --> 16:31.000
To prison.

16:31.000 --> 16:33.000
I don't understand.

16:33.000 --> 16:35.000
What's the problem here?

16:35.000 --> 16:37.000
Stop.

16:37.000 --> 16:39.000
This man is from my family.

16:39.000 --> 16:41.000
What's the problem?

16:41.000 --> 16:44.000
He didn't stop for the hat.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
He doesn't love the emperor.

16:46.000 --> 16:50.000
Friends, look at this.

16:50.000 --> 16:55.000
Do we want a hat on a tree in our streets?

16:55.000 --> 16:58.000
Is this an emperor?

16:58.000 --> 17:02.000
You can't take William Tell away.

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
He's a man of peace.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
Don't take Tell.

17:06.000 --> 17:10.000
The governor is coming.

17:10.000 --> 17:14.000
Is there a problem here?

17:14.000 --> 17:16.000
Yes, governor.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.000
This man and his son didn't stop for your hat.

17:21.000 --> 17:24.000
We're taking them to prison.

17:24.000 --> 17:30.000
But the people of the town are with him, not us.

17:30.000 --> 17:32.000
Is the hat important?

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
I'm sorry, governor.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
But there's no problem.

17:36.000 --> 17:43.000
This afternoon, tomorrow, and every day I'm going to stop and look up at your hat.

17:43.000 --> 17:46.000
I want peace in our store.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.000
And in all of Switzerland.

17:48.000 --> 17:50.000
William Tell.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
You're a difficult man.

17:52.000 --> 17:56.000
And you have your crossbow with you again.

17:56.000 --> 18:02.000
My father can hit an apple on a tree from a hundred feet with his crossbow.

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
Can he?

18:04.000 --> 18:11.000
Soldier, bring me an apple.

18:11.000 --> 18:13.000
Good.

18:13.000 --> 18:14.000
Tell.

18:14.000 --> 18:22.000
Take your son to that tree across the street and put this apple on his head.

18:22.000 --> 18:26.000
Then take your crossbow and walk away.

18:26.000 --> 18:31.000
Hit the apple and you and your son can live.

18:31.000 --> 18:34.000
On my son's head.

18:34.000 --> 18:37.000
No father can do that.

18:37.000 --> 18:38.000
Kill me now.

18:38.000 --> 18:39.000
No.

18:39.000 --> 18:40.000
Do it.

18:40.000 --> 18:44.000
You and your crossbow are famous.

18:44.000 --> 18:51.000
Boy, stand near the tree and wait for your father's arrow.

18:51.000 --> 18:53.000
Governor, stop.

18:53.000 --> 18:56.000
Take my money and my house.

18:56.000 --> 18:59.000
But don't kill Tell and Walter.

18:59.000 --> 19:02.000
I'm going to be okay.

19:02.000 --> 19:04.000
Father can hit this apple.

19:04.000 --> 19:07.000
There's no problem.

19:07.000 --> 19:08.000
Tell.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.000
Wait.

19:09.000 --> 19:14.000
Your hand is moving and your eyes are swimming in your head.

19:14.000 --> 19:18.000
Don't play this man's games, Governor.

19:18.000 --> 19:19.000
Kill me.

19:19.000 --> 19:21.000
Not my son.

19:21.000 --> 19:25.000
I want to watch you with your crossbow.

19:25.000 --> 19:26.000
Do it.

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
Father, you can do it.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
I'm going to be okay.

19:30.000 --> 19:31.000
Yes.

19:31.000 --> 19:33.000
You can do it, Tell.

19:33.000 --> 19:34.000
You're a hero.

19:34.000 --> 19:36.000
Tells our man.

19:36.000 --> 19:39.000
We don't want that hat on the tree.

19:39.000 --> 19:40.000
Tell.

19:40.000 --> 19:43.000
Hit the apple and go home.

19:43.000 --> 19:44.000
Look.

19:44.000 --> 19:47.000
Your son is waiting.

19:47.000 --> 19:49.000
You can do it, Father.

19:59.000 --> 20:02.000
They did it.

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
Look, Father.

20:04.000 --> 20:05.000
I'm okay.

20:05.000 --> 20:07.000
I'm not dead.

20:07.000 --> 20:14.000
Every Swiss man, woman and child is going to hear about William Tell.

20:14.000 --> 20:16.000
He's our hero.

20:16.000 --> 20:18.000
Tell could hit an apple.

20:18.000 --> 20:20.000
Or a soldier.

20:20.000 --> 20:24.000
Walter, William, let's go to my house.

20:24.000 --> 20:25.000
Come with me.

20:25.000 --> 20:26.000
Stop.

20:26.000 --> 20:29.000
I want to talk to Tell.

20:29.000 --> 20:31.000
Yes, Governor.

20:31.000 --> 20:33.000
Good job, Tell.

20:33.000 --> 20:39.000
But where's your second arrow in my shirt?

20:39.000 --> 20:43.000
Why did you have a second arrow?

20:43.000 --> 20:45.000
It was for you.

20:45.000 --> 20:48.000
A dead governor for a dead son.

20:48.000 --> 20:54.000
But now the arrow can stay in my shirt and I can go home.

20:54.000 --> 20:55.000
Goodbye.

20:55.000 --> 20:58.000
An arrow for me.

20:58.000 --> 21:01.000
Soldiers, take him to prison.

21:01.000 --> 21:04.000
He's not going to walk away from me.

21:04.000 --> 21:05.000
No.

21:05.000 --> 21:06.000
Wait.

21:06.000 --> 21:08.000
He's a good man.

21:08.000 --> 21:10.000
He's a man of peace.

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
He's our hero.

21:12.000 --> 21:17.000
You're a very bad man, Governor Gessler.

21:17.000 --> 21:20.000
I'm not going to kill you, Tell.

21:20.000 --> 21:23.000
But you're dangerous.

21:23.000 --> 21:25.000
I'm going to put you in prison.

21:25.000 --> 21:27.000
In Kusnacht.

21:27.000 --> 21:31.000
I don't want you and your crossbow on these streets.

21:31.000 --> 21:34.000
Soldiers, take him to my boat.

21:43.000 --> 21:45.000
Scene eight.

21:45.000 --> 21:47.000
On the governor's boat.

21:48.000 --> 21:56.000
Why is Tell important to the governor?

21:56.000 --> 21:59.000
He's very good with the crossbow.

21:59.000 --> 22:03.000
And he's a hero to the Swiss people.

22:03.000 --> 22:06.000
The governor doesn't like it.

22:06.000 --> 22:10.000
But the Swiss people love him now.

22:10.000 --> 22:14.000
Look at this rain.

22:14.000 --> 22:17.000
It's very dangerous on the water.

22:17.000 --> 22:20.000
Where's our hero now?

22:20.000 --> 22:24.000
We're never going to arrive at Kusnacht.

22:24.000 --> 22:26.000
Where's my boat, man?

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
Here I am, Governor.

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
What's wrong?

22:30.000 --> 22:32.000
And when are we going to arrive?

22:32.000 --> 22:35.000
The rain's very heavy, Governor.

22:35.000 --> 22:37.000
And the water's dangerous.

22:37.000 --> 22:40.000
I'm not a strong man.

22:40.000 --> 22:43.000
I'm having problems with the boats.

22:43.000 --> 22:46.000
Soldiers, help the boat, man.

22:46.000 --> 22:49.000
What do they know about boats?

22:49.000 --> 22:50.000
Get some help.

22:50.000 --> 22:51.000
Now!

22:51.000 --> 22:55.000
The prisoner tells good with boats.

22:55.000 --> 22:58.000
Bring the prisoner to me.

23:03.000 --> 23:04.000
Tell!

23:04.000 --> 23:06.000
Help us with this boat.

23:06.000 --> 23:08.000
How can I help you?

23:08.000 --> 23:09.000
Look at me.

23:09.000 --> 23:12.000
I'm a prisoner, not a boatman.

23:12.000 --> 23:15.000
You're not a prisoner now, tell.

23:15.000 --> 23:20.000
Boatman, here's your helper.

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
Here we are!

23:28.000 --> 23:32.000
Soldiers, take tell to the prison.

23:32.000 --> 23:34.000
What? Prison?

23:34.000 --> 23:35.000
No.

23:35.000 --> 23:39.000
I'm going to take my crossbow and say goodbye.

23:39.000 --> 23:41.000
Where did he go?

23:42.000 --> 23:44.000
He helped us.

23:44.000 --> 23:47.000
And now he's going to help his people.

23:47.000 --> 23:49.000
He is a hero.

23:49.000 --> 23:51.000
Stop him!

23:51.000 --> 23:55.000
In Anstoff, he wanted to kill me.

23:55.000 --> 23:57.000
But we can't see him.

23:57.000 --> 23:59.000
But I can see you.

24:03.000 --> 24:04.000
Oh no.

24:04.000 --> 24:06.000
The governor's dead.

24:06.000 --> 24:08.000
Where's Tell?

24:08.000 --> 24:10.000
He's in the mountains now.

24:10.000 --> 24:13.000
We can never find him.

24:13.000 --> 24:18.000
Let's take our dead governor to his house in Kursnach.

24:24.000 --> 24:28.000
Scene 9, in a street in Anstoff.

24:30.000 --> 24:33.000
William, you're back!

24:33.000 --> 24:37.000
How did you get away from Gessler and his soldiers?

24:37.000 --> 24:40.000
They helped them with their boat on a very bad night.

24:40.000 --> 24:43.000
Then I killed the governor.

24:43.000 --> 24:45.000
Yes.

24:45.000 --> 24:49.000
Now things are going to be good again in our country.

24:49.000 --> 24:51.000
Gessler's dead.

24:51.000 --> 24:54.000
But we must finish Tell's work.

24:54.000 --> 24:58.000
We must send the Austrians back to their home.

24:58.000 --> 25:01.000
Let's start our fight today.

25:01.000 --> 25:04.000
Tell your our hero.

25:04.000 --> 25:06.000
Can you help us again?

25:06.000 --> 25:07.000
Of course I can.

25:07.000 --> 25:12.000
Every Swiss person is going to fight for their country.

25:12.000 --> 25:18.000
Many years from now, our children's children are going to talk about our fight.

25:21.000 --> 25:23.000
He's Gessler's hat.

25:23.000 --> 25:25.000
What can we do with that?

25:25.000 --> 25:27.000
Do we want it?

25:27.000 --> 25:29.000
Put it in the river.

25:29.000 --> 25:31.000
Send it to Austria!

25:31.000 --> 25:32.000
Wait!

25:33.000 --> 25:36.000
Let's put it in an important place.

25:36.000 --> 25:40.000
Let's look at it every day and remember Gessler.

25:40.000 --> 25:43.000
Let's say never again.

25:43.000 --> 25:45.000
Switzerland is for the Swiss.

25:45.000 --> 25:47.000
Yeah.

25:47.000 --> 25:51.000
But isn't the emperor going to look for you?

25:51.000 --> 25:54.000
Isn't he going to come here with his soldiers?

25:54.000 --> 25:56.000
Yes.

25:56.000 --> 26:00.000
Gessler was his friend and one of his governors.

26:00.000 --> 26:02.000
But we're strong.

26:02.000 --> 26:04.000
And we can stop the soldiers.

26:04.000 --> 26:08.000
We can wait for them in the mountains.

26:08.000 --> 26:10.000
We must listen to William Tell.

26:10.000 --> 26:11.000
You're right.

26:11.000 --> 26:13.000
But wait.

26:13.000 --> 26:14.000
Who's coming?

26:14.000 --> 26:16.000
It's Staufacher.

26:16.000 --> 26:18.000
Listen.

26:18.000 --> 26:21.000
The emperor is dead.

26:21.000 --> 26:22.000
What?

26:22.000 --> 26:23.000
How?

26:23.000 --> 26:24.000
When?

26:24.000 --> 26:29.000
Many Austrian people didn't like Gessler or the emperor.

26:29.000 --> 26:34.000
The emperor was on the road to Baden here in Switzerland.

26:34.000 --> 26:38.000
Some Austrians stopped him and killed him.

26:38.000 --> 26:41.000
Then they went back to Austria.

26:41.000 --> 26:45.000
This is a good day for our country.

26:45.000 --> 26:48.000
Now, we've got an important job.

26:48.000 --> 26:52.000
We must build a strong Switzerland.

26:52.000 --> 26:55.000
We can have peace now.

26:55.000 --> 26:57.000
Goodbye, my friends.

26:57.000 --> 27:02.000
I'm going home to the mountains and to my family.

27:02.000 --> 27:04.000
Thank you, William.

27:04.000 --> 27:08.000
Switzerland is always going to remember you.

27:08.000 --> 27:11.000
You're our hero!

27:11.000 --> 27:13.000
William Tell!

